    }
    rating: "Pretty Good"
    comments: "The dialogue is pretty standard for an 80s movie, but has some iconic lines and moments; the humor is pretty standard; the symbolism is pretty simple as it is about two brothers bonding, but the movie does bring awareness to Autism (which was pretty groundbreaking for the time, even though it can be stereotypical at times); the foreshadowing is pretty standard for an 80s movie"
